# flotilla-doctor host paths — consumed by deploy/flotilla-doctor-install.sh to
# generate ~/.config/systemd/user/flotilla-doctor.service from
# deploy/flotilla-doctor.service.in, and to copy the escalator script + timer.
#
# SETUP (one-time per host):
#   cp deploy/flotilla-doctor.env.example deploy/flotilla-doctor.env
#   $EDITOR deploy/flotilla-doctor.env       # set the paths for THIS host
#   bash deploy/flotilla-doctor-install.sh   # generate + install unit/script/timer
#   systemctl --user enable --now flotilla-doctor.timer
#
# deploy/flotilla-doctor.env is gitignored: these are filesystem paths (NOT secrets),
# but the layout is per-host, so each host keeps its own. To change paths later, edit
# this file and re-run the installer — never hand-edit the installed unit.
#
# Paths may use the systemd specifier %h (your home directory) IN THE UNIT'S
# WorkingDirectory only; the doctor script's ExecStart flags are passed to a bash
# script that runs `"$BIN"` / `"$CLAUDE"` directly, so a LITERAL absolute path is
# safer there than %h (bash does not expand %h). The example below uses literal paths.
# Values are taken LITERALLY — do NOT quote them; whitespace around `=` is trimmed.

# ---- required (these become @PLACEHOLDER@ substitutions in the unit) ----

# Where the installer COPIES deploy/flotilla-doctor.sh (the escalator) and what the
# unit's ExecStart runs. A stable per-user path.
FLOTILLA_DOCTOR_DEST=%h/.local/bin/flotilla-doctor

# The `--from` identity for the operator notify (a webhook name in the secrets file).
FLOTILLA_SELF=xo

# Secrets file (chmod 600) holding FLOTILLA_WEBHOOK_<SELF> for the notify post.
FLOTILLA_SECRETS=%h/.config/flotilla/flotilla-secrets.env

# Working directory for the doctor run AND the cwd the recovery agent runs in (so the
# recover-flotilla skill's `flotilla notify --secrets state/...` resolves). Your fleet's
# repo/state root, where state/flotilla*.{json,env} live.
FLOTILLA_WORKDIR=%h/.config/flotilla

# The flotilla binary (used for the best-effort operator notify on escalation).
FLOTILLA_BIN=%h/go/bin/flotilla

# The claude binary the escalator spawns headless: `claude --print "/<skill> …"`.
FLOTILLA_CLAUDE_BIN=%h/.local/bin/claude

# The recovery skill name the escalator invokes (`/<skill> <status>`).
FLOTILLA_RECOVER_SKILL=recover-flotilla

# State dir for the doctor's lock/strike/cooldown files + its log. Your fleet's state
# root is a natural home (the same place flotilla's ack file and roster live).
FLOTILLA_DOCTOR_STATE_DIR=%h/.config/flotilla

# ---- optional tunables (the script defaults all of these; the generated unit
#      uses the defaults). NOTE: these keys are NOT consumed by the installer —
#      setting them in THIS file has no effect. To change them, edit
#      deploy/flotilla-doctor.service.in and re-run the installer:
#        * --threshold / --cooldown / --recheck  -> add the flag to the ExecStart line
#        * the env-only knobs below               -> add an `Environment=` line
#      The defaults (shown) are the right values for the standard 3-min cadence.
#
#   --threshold 3       confirmed-down strikes before escalating (cadence 3min × 3 ≈ ~9 min)
#   --cooldown 1800     seconds to suppress re-spawning the recovery agent after an escalation
#   --recheck 15        seconds to wait before the single confirm-recheck after a down read
#   Environment=FLOTILLA_DOCTOR_STRIKE_STALE=600    strikes older than this restart the window at 0
#   Environment=FLOTILLA_DOCTOR_CLAUDE_TIMEOUT=600  wall-clock cap (s) on the recovery agent
#
# TIMEOUT COUPLING — IMPORTANT: a single doctor run can sleep --recheck seconds AND,
# on escalation, run the recovery agent for up to FLOTILLA_DOCTOR_CLAUDE_TIMEOUT
# seconds. The unit's TimeoutStartSec (deploy/flotilla-doctor.service.in, default
# 700) must cover recheck + claude_timeout + margin, or systemd will SIGTERM a
# recovery mid-flight. If you raise FLOTILLA_DOCTOR_CLAUDE_TIMEOUT or --recheck,
# raise TimeoutStartSec in flotilla-doctor.service.in to match, then re-run the installer.
